cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.GT

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper investigates optimizing utility-energy efficiency in a heterogeneous network, which falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture.
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper applies Lagrangian dual analysis with auxiliary variables to transform the subproblems to convex ones, which is a technique commonly used in information theory.
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The power control aspect of the problem can be related to systems and control.
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The heterogeneous network may involve multimedia traffic, which could be a potential application of the proposed algorithm.
5. cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) - The concept of utility can be related to game theory, which could be a potential application of the proposed algorithm.
